https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Strict_mode

use strict throws errors in the following cases
1. Assigning to NaN, undefined
2. creating variables without using let, var or const (ex: num = 5)
    without use strict this kind of declaration is valid..as the variable gets created in global scope
3. strict mode makes attempts to delete undeletable properties throw (where before the attempt would have no effect):
4. strict mode requires that function parameter names be unique.
5. a strict mode in ECMAScript 5 forbids a 0-prefixed octal literal or octal escape sequence.
6. strict mode in ECMAScript 2015 forbids setting properties on primitive values.